<center>
   <br><br>
   <h1>JSP as XML Documents</h1>
   <br>
</center> 
<font size=4>
<ul>
   <li>Every JSP tag can be written in XML format in replacement of the
       JSP standard syntax.</li>
   <ul>
      <li>Scriptlets</li>
      <ul>
         <li>JSP: <font color="red">&lt% code %></font></li>
         <li>XML: <font color="red">&ltjsp:scriplet >
             code &lt/jsp:scriplet></font></li>
      </ul>
      <li>Expressions</li>
      <ul>
         <li>JSP: <font color="red">&lt%= code %></font></li>
         <li>XML: <font color="red">&ltjsp:expression > code
             &lt/jsp:expression></font></li>
      </ul>
      <li>Declarations</li>
      <ul>
         <li>JSP: <font color="red">&lt%! code %></font></li>
         <li>XML: <font color="red">&ltjsp:declaration> code
             &lt/jsp:expression></font></li>
      </ul>
      <li>Actions</li>
      <ul>
         <li>XML: <font color="red">&ltjsp:action_name attribute="value
             /></font></li>
      </ul>
      <li>Directives</li>
      <ul>
         <li>JSP: <font color="red">&lt%@ directive_name %></font></li>
         <li>XML: <font color="red">&ltjsp:directive.directive_name
             /></font></li>
      </ul>
      <li>Comments</li>
      <ul>
         <li>JSP: <font color="red">&lt%-- comment --%></font></li>
         <li>XML: <font color="red">&lt!-- comment --></font></li>
      </ul>
   <li>Converting from 
       <a href="jspformat.html">JSP Format</a> to 
       <a href="xmlformat.html">XML Format</a> is fairly
       straightforward.</li>
   <li>Java XML Parsers</li>
   <ul>
      <li>JAXP - <a href="http://java.sun.com/xml/">
          http://java.sun.com/xml</a></li>
      <li>Oracle XML Parser - 
          <a href="http://technet.oracle.com/tech/xml/parser_java2/">
          http://technet.oracle.com/tech/xml/parser_java2</a></li>
   </ul>
</ul>
</font>
</html>

